  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>change in thymic size</measure>
    <time_frame>1 year</time_frame>
    <description>A clinically meaningful change is defined as increase in thymic size (&gt; 0.2cm increase in uni-dimensional diameter), functional volume (&gt;10%) or uptake (≥25%). We will report proportion of patients with each component of clinically meaningful change, as well as the proportion with at least one component, along 95% exact confidence intervals.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <number_of_groups>1</number_of_groups>
  <enrollment type="Actual">3</enrollment>
  <condition>CD34 Selected Peripheral Blood Stem Cell Graft</condition>
  <arm_group>
    <arm_group_label>PET/CT scans and MRI</arm_group_label>
    <description>Eligible patients will be enrolled onto the study, and will undergo 3 limited field of view (FOV) FDG-PET/CT scans and MRI of the chest: at baseline (within 4 weeks prior to transplantation), and approximately 3 months (+/-2 weeks) and 6 months (+/-2 weeks) after transplant. PET/CT and MR imaging can be completed on the same day. We will also offer the exams on other days if this is easier for the patient. The PET/CT and MR should be performed within 2 weeks of each other.</description>
  </arm_group>
